s lost in 2D projections. However, biological structures such as DNA and proteins consistently exhibit right-handedness [ 33 ]. Thus, we assumed consistent chirality when comparing their configurations. Simulation experiments showed that parameter changes had little effect on chirality distribution, with each configuration stabilized at       \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
