T data. It identifies 2D transcription centers as expression-weighted geometric centers of transcriptional spots per gene, treating these as noisy projections of the underlying 3D configuration.  Cytocraft iteratively alternates between the F-step (updating configuration given rotations) and R-step (refining rotations given configuration), minimizing distance between projected and observed transcription centers to recover the latent spatial configuration.    Estimating transcription centers  From SST data of       \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
